<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 03 at 5:59PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Scotland,
southeastern Richmond and southern Hoke Counties through 645 PM
EDT...
At 559 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurinburg, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Raeford, Hamlet, Maxton, Antioch, Dobbins Heights,
Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg and Laurel Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
